Rotating $\triangle ABC$ around leg $\overline{CB}$ produces a cone with radius 3 cm, height 4 cm, and volume \[\frac{1}{3}\pi(3^2)(4)=12\pi\] cubic cm.  [asy]
size(110);
import solids; defaultpen(linewidth(0.8)); currentprojection = orthographic(5,0,1);
revolution c = cone((0,0,0), 3, 4);
draw(c,heavycyan);
draw((0,0,0)--(0,3,0)--(0,0,4)--cycle);
label("$B$",(0,0,0),SW); label("$A$",(0,3,0),SE); label("$C$",(0,0,4),N);

label("3",(0,1.5,0),S); label("4",(0,0,2),W);
[/asy]

Rotating $\triangle ABC$ around leg $\overline{AB}$ produces a cone with radius 4 cm, height 3 cm, and volume \[\frac{1}{3}\pi(4^2)(3)=16\pi\] cubic cm.  [asy]
import solids; currentprojection = orthographic(5,0,1);
revolution c = cone((0,0,0), 4, 3);
draw(c,heavycyan);
draw((0,0,0)--(0,4,0)--(0,0,3)--cycle);
label("$B$",(0,0,0),SW); label("$C$",(0,4,0),SE); label("$A$",(0,0,3),N);

label("4",(0,2,0),S); label("3",(0,0,1.5),W);
[/asy]

$16\pi\approx 50.27$ cubic cm is the greater volume.  To the nearest whole number, this value is $\boxed{50}$ cubic cm.
